         <TR BGCOLOR="#000000"><Td ALIGN="LEFT">
         <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana" COLOR="#c0c0c0">
         <blockquote>
         You simply don't understand the basic theory here.  NWN was a completely different gaming environment.  NWN created a small, close knit gaming community centered around a simple game that provided endless amusement and incredibly intricate possibilities.  That environment is gone.  You may think recreating it on your Palm Pilot and comparing it to Pong and Tetris is the solution however, that's moronic.  Pong and Tetris are/were simple games.  NWN was very, very complex.  <P>Am I arguing that NWN was perfect in every facet?  Hell no, it had plenty of flaws, however, the style of gaming it created was vastly superior to the current incarnations.  NWN represented a gaming pillar taken to its highest possible level.  Gold Box games had come as close to reaching a limit as possible with the final evolution of NWN.<P>The current style of MMORPGs (IE UO, EQ, SB to come, et al)  is a completely different platform.  The playerbase is much larger, the PvP almost opposite that of NWN, many different character types are popular, etc.  I would say this crop hasn't evolved to anywhere near its potential.  <P>NWN represents a different sort of game, a sort I feel was vastly superior.  Maybe SB will evolve well past EQ and prove that NWN was only a quality game by 1995 standards.  Or maybe the unbelievably queer model of EQ is as good as it gets, in which case someone better fucking bring back the Gold Box games.<P>Fat Kid<BR>KAAOS
         </blockquote>
